This is a known breaking change. .NET 10 MAUI adopts **edge-to-edge** rendering on Android (required by Android 15+), which makes the deprecated `AdjustResize` soft input mode no longer function. You need to use the **WindowInsets API** instead.

### The fix

React to IME (keyboard) insets in your Android platform code and apply bottom padding to your page:

**1. In `Platforms/Android/MainActivity.cs`:**

```csharp
using Android.Views;
using AndroidX.Core.View;
using Microsoft.Maui.Platform;

public class MainActivity : MauiAppCompatActivity
{
    protected override void OnCreate(Bundle? savedInstanceState)
    {
        base.OnCreate(savedInstanceState);

        // Listen for keyboard (IME) inset changes
        ViewCompat.SetOnApplyWindowInsetsListener(
            Window!.DecorView, new KeyboardInsetsListener());
    }

    private class KeyboardInsetsListener : Java.Lang.Object, IOnApplyWindowInsetsListener
    {
        public WindowInsetsCompat OnApplyWindowInsets(View view, WindowInsetsCompat insets)
        {
            var imeInsets = insets.GetInsets(WindowInsetsCompat.Type.Ime());
            var navBarInsets = insets.GetInsets(WindowInsetsCompat.Type.NavigationBars());

            // Use IME bottom when keyboard is visible, otherwise nav bar bottom
            int bottomPx = Math.Max(imeInsets.Bottom, navBarInsets.Bottom);

            // Convert px → DIPs for MAUI
            float density = view.Context!.Resources!.DisplayMetrics!.Density;
            double bottomDip = bottomPx / density;

            // Push the content up by setting padding on the current page
            var page = Application.Current?.MainPage;
            if (page is Shell shell)
                page = shell.CurrentPage;

            if (page != null)
                page.Padding = new Thickness(0, 0, 0, bottomDip);

            return insets;
        }
    }
}
```

**2. Your chat page XAML (simplified):**

```xml
<ContentPage xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui" ...>
  <Grid RowDefinitions="*,Auto">
    <CollectionView Grid.Row="0" ItemsSource="{Binding Messages}" ... />

    <HorizontalStackLayout Grid.Row="1" Padding="8">
      <Entry Placeholder="Type a message..." HorizontalOptions="FillAndExpand" />
      <Button Text="Send" />
    </HorizontalStackLayout>
  </Grid>
</ContentPage>
```

### Why this works

| .NET 9 (old) | .NET 10 (new) |
|---|---|
| `AdjustResize` shrinks the window | Window is always edge-to-edge |
| OS handled layout shift | **You** respond to `WindowInsets` |

The `Ime()` inset tells you exactly how tall the keyboard is. When it closes, `imeInsets.Bottom` returns to `0` and the nav-bar inset takes over, so your layout snaps back automatically.

### iOS

No change needed — iOS MAUI already adjusts for the keyboard via `UIScrollView` behavior. If you do hit issues, wrap your layout in a `ScrollView` with `KeyboardDismissMode="OnDrag"`.
